theorem closure_interior_closure_eq_closure_of_isOpen
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (hA : IsOpen (A : Set X)) :
    closure (interior (closure (A : Set X))) = closure (A : Set X) := by
  -- Step 1:  Show `A ⊆ interior (closure A)`.
  have hA_sub : (A : Set X) ⊆ interior (closure (A : Set X)) := by
    intro x hxA
    -- Since `A` is open, `x` is an interior point of `A`.
    have hxIntA : x ∈ interior (A : Set X) := by
      simpa [hA.interior_eq] using hxA
    -- Monotonicity of `interior` along the inclusion `A ⊆ closure A`.
    have hMono : interior (A : Set X) ⊆ interior (closure (A : Set X)) :=
      interior_mono (subset_closure : (A : Set X) ⊆ closure (A : Set X))
    exact hMono hxIntA
  -- Taking closures yields one inclusion of the desired equality.
  have h₁ : closure (A : Set X) ⊆ closure (interior (closure (A : Set X))) :=
    closure_mono hA_sub
  -- Step 2:  The reverse inclusion is immediate by monotonicity of `closure`.
  have h₂ :
      closure (interior (closure (A : Set X))) ⊆ closure (A : Set X) := by
    have : interior (closure (A : Set X)) ⊆ closure (A : Set X) :=
      interior_subset
    exact closure_mono this
  -- Combine the two inclusions to obtain the equality.
  exact Set.Subset.antisymm h₂ h₁

theorem P1_subset_closure_interior {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    Topology.P1 A → (A : Set X) ⊆ closure (interior A) := by
  intro hP1
  simpa [Topology.P1] using hP1
